    {
      "id": "2DZh5l2AoTn_vcTZPjf6e",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 135.5177061334996,
      "y": 3502.730495363612,
      "width": 166.0749599845185,
      "height": 275,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#b2f2bb",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b6o",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 2127460152,
      "version": 439,
      "versionNonce": 355247432,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1768572608729,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Green: Durable\nasync replicated\nStorage to\nRegion B\n\nRed: Hot Path\nfor users acting\nagainst\nInferences in\nthe Tenant\nResources. ",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Green: Durable async replicated Storage to Region B\n\nRed: Hot Path for users acting against Inferences in the Tenant Resources. ",
      "autoResize": false,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "Tu9r_qAsJ5ifjZNmlw2Wc",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 648.5701561152014,
      "y": 3858.0978804750625,
      "width": 1621.7944950015972,
      "height": 1700,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffc9c9",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b6p",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 93738312,
      "version": 5298,
      "versionNonce": 1983153736,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1768512140600,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Primary write/execute: \n    Emit telemetry: \n        Tenant LB routes the request to most underutilized inference within the tenant namespace with the required model by least connections\n        Payload is processed by the Inference and provided to the model.\n        Payload is produced to the Inference Telemetry system w/ no ack. (best-effort)\n        Response from model is provided to the Inference.\n        Response from mode is produced to the Telemetry system w/ ack.\n        Inference responds to gateway request with response from model. \n    Rollback on trigger:\n        Product User publishes rollback.\n        API Service receives rollback request with text for reasoning, tenant, and ENV.\n        API Service fetches Previous functional Version per ENV available for backout from RDBMS.\n        API Service updates RDBMS approval table with previous version + reason \n        API receives ACK from RDBMS\n        Triggers <Approve/publish rollout>\n        API Service updates Audit Service with approval request, new version, on tenant and env, + reason.\n    Serve inference + enforce admission:\n        User sends a request payload defining tenant needed and Model Request.\n        API Gateway intercepts the payload and validates AuthN.\n        API Gateway validates AuthZ and Budget per payload tenant defined.\n        API Gateway chooses to block tenant or not.\n        If not API Gateway sends request to tenant LB based on routing rules.\n        Tenant LB routes the request to most underutilized inference within the tenant namespace with the required model by least connections\nPrimary read:\n\nControl-plane change path:\n    Create/update desired state\n        Product User requests access through the API Gateway.\n        API Gateway performs AuthN.\n        API Gateway perform sAuthZ and routes to available tenants based on AD-Groups to API Services.\n        API Services fetch available tenants per Product User\n        Product User chooses tenant\n        API Service fetches current Inferences per tenant/env and the models being served\n        API Service async fetches from Version Config from Version Object Storage\n        Product User chooses tenant/env \n        API Service populates the version config from Version Object Storage\n        Product User edits and publishes update w/ notes on the change\n        API Service performs an atomic lock on the RDBMS approval table with new version + notes \n        API Service populates Version Object Storage with new version/metadata and config into Version Object Storage\n        API receives ACK from RDBMS\n        Triggers <Approve/publish rollout>\n        API Service updates Audit Service with approval request, new version, on tenant and env, + notes.\n    Approve/publish rollout\n        Product Approval Owner requests access through the API Gateway.\n        API Gateway performs AuthN.\n        API Gateway perform sAuthZ and routes to available tenants based on AD-Groups to API Services.\n        API Services fetch available tenants per Product User\n        Product Approval Owner chooses tenant\n        API Service fetches current Inferences per tenant/env and the models being served plus pending approvals\n        Product Approval Owner chooses the tenant/env pending approval request\n        API Service starts an atomic update against the RDBMS with new version, status(queued) in authoritative table for Inferences.\n        Product Approval Owner chooses approval \n        API Commits the atomic update\n        RDBMS triggers message in Reconciliation Queue\n        API receives ACK from RDBMS\n        API Service updates Audit Service with new version, on tenant and env, + notes.\n        <Reconcile to serving begins>         \n    Reconcile to serving\n        Controllers prioritize consuming from priority queue over rollout queue\n        Controllers route through the API Gateway and create a secure traffic pipe when communicating with the K8 API inside of the Cluster\n        Controllers execute messages against tenant resources in stages(Consumed, Running, Finished) updating the authoritative table and audit each time\n            Notes: \n                The status changes are required for observability and troubleshooting. \n                A single tenant can have multiple models running at the same time in a env but they also control traffic routing when they edit the payload.\n        \n       \n\n        ",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Primary write/execute: \n    Emit telemetry: \n        Tenant LB routes the request to most underutilized inference within the tenant namespace with the required model by least connections\n        Payload is processed by the Inference and provided to the model.\n        Payload is produced to the Inference Telemetry system w/ no ack. (best-effort)\n        Response from model is provided to the Inference.\n        Response from mode is produced to the Telemetry system w/ ack.\n        Inference responds to gateway request with response from model. \n    Rollback on trigger:\n        Product User publishes rollback.\n        API Service receives rollback request with text for reasoning, tenant, and ENV.\n        API Service fetches Previous functional Version per ENV available for backout from RDBMS.\n        API Service updates RDBMS approval table with previous version + reason \n        API receives ACK from RDBMS\n        Triggers <Approve/publish rollout>\n        API Service updates Audit Service with approval request, new version, on tenant and env, + reason.\n    Serve inference + enforce admission:\n        User sends a request payload defining tenant needed and Model Request.\n        API Gateway intercepts the payload and validates AuthN.\n        API Gateway validates AuthZ and Budget per payload tenant defined.\n        API Gateway chooses to block tenant or not.\n        If not API Gateway sends request to tenant LB based on routing rules.\n        Tenant LB routes the request to most underutilized inference within the tenant namespace with the required model by least connections\nPrimary read:\n\nControl-plane change path:\n    Create/update desired state\n        Product User requests access through the API Gateway.\n        API Gateway performs AuthN.\n        API Gateway perform sAuthZ and routes to available tenants based on AD-Groups to API Services.\n        API Services fetch available tenants per Product User\n        Product User chooses tenant\n        API Service fetches current Inferences per tenant/env and the models being served\n        API Service async fetches from Version Config from Version Object Storage\n        Product User chooses tenant/env \n        API Service populates the version config from Version Object Storage\n        Product User edits and publishes update w/ notes on the change\n        API Service performs an atomic lock on the RDBMS approval table with new version + notes \n        API Service populates Version Object Storage with new version/metadata and config into Version Object Storage\n        API receives ACK from RDBMS\n        Triggers <Approve/publish rollout>\n        API Service updates Audit Service with approval request, new version, on tenant and env, + notes.\n    Approve/publish rollout\n        Product Approval Owner requests access through the API Gateway.\n        API Gateway performs AuthN.\n        API Gateway perform sAuthZ and routes to available tenants based on AD-Groups to API Services.\n        API Services fetch available tenants per Product User\n        Product Approval Owner chooses tenant\n        API Service fetches current Inferences per tenant/env and the models being served plus pending approvals\n        Product Approval Owner chooses the tenant/env pending approval request\n        API Service starts an atomic update against the RDBMS with new version, status(queued) in authoritative table for Inferences.\n        Product Approval Owner chooses approval \n        API Commits the atomic update\n        RDBMS triggers message in Reconciliation Queue\n        API receives ACK from RDBMS\n        API Service updates Audit Service with new version, on tenant and env, + notes.\n        <Reconcile to serving begins>         \n    Reconcile to serving\n        Controllers prioritize consuming from priority queue over rollout queue\n        Controllers route through the API Gateway and create a secure traffic pipe when communicating with the K8 API inside of the Cluster\n        Controllers execute messages against tenant resources in stages(Consumed, Running, Finished) updating the authoritative table and audit each time\n            Notes: \n                The status changes are required for observability and troubleshooting. \n                A single tenant can have multiple models running at the same time in a env but they also control traffic routing when they edit the payload.\n        \n       \n\n        ",
      "autoResize": false,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
