      "updated": 1768832084951,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "FR:\n    Jobs Definition:\n        Must support multiple ordered stages\n        Must support an immutable per build version\n    Jobs Execution:\n        Must be able to Submit and Cancel Jobs via API\n        Must be able to track execution status and stages \n        Must support configuration for retry and TTL Windows(fairness) per retry\n        Observe Job Resources(Metrics, Logs, Alerts) for Tenants\n        Must support audit\n    Tenants:\n        Must support quotas(manage runaway compute)\n        Chargeback per Hour observability for Cost Awareness emitted to global object store \n    Resource Sharing:\n        Must enforce Resource Access Control to prevent critical resources bottlenecks\n        Must enforce locking per resource region, this does not cover multi-region resource locks\n        Must support fairness queues & rate limits across tenants  \n    Clusters:\n        Configure Cluster Resources and Quotas\n        Observe Cluster Resources(Metrics, Logs, Alerts) for Platform Teams\n\nNFRs:\n    Availability: CP 99.99%, DP Globally 99.999%(w/ failover), This only includes admitted jobs only\n    RPO/RTO: CP Job Build (RPO < 1 minute, RTO < 3 hours), CP Job Scheduling ( RPO < 5 minutes, RTO < 30 minutes), CP Cluster/Tenant Config(RPO < 5 minutes, RTO < 30 minutes), DP\nClusters ( RPO < 1 minute, RTO < 24 hours )\n    Scale: Multi-Region Active/Active; Tenants(100), Concurrent Jobs(p50<1,000, p99<10,000), Regional Locks; tenant scheduling budgets; resource retry budgets/circuit breakers.\n    Latency: Admitted-Jobs (p50<1 second, p95<5) from accepted response to starting job execution; On failover additional 5 minutes required. \n    Operability: Golden Signals(latency, traffic, errors, saturation) per tenant and global; budget trends create ticket; SLO Burn-Rate Paging; \n    Security: Authentication and Authorization; enforced quotas; tenant isolation; mTLS across all components; immutable audit store\n\nScope: \n    Not Included: Build system, artifact storage, approvals, UI, central observability ingestion, time-based scheduled triggers, global(not regional) shared resource locking, Jobs that span across\nregions\n\nInvariants:\nIdempotent Jobs: No single iteration(attempt_id) of a job can run in multiple regions. Every retry of a job is a new attempt_id of that job and is generated by the system.\nJob Retry Fairness: Retries must not preempt older admitted work by queue position across tenants \nTenant Isolation: If a tenant exceeds budget requests are rejected, never oversubscribed.\nJob Submission Persistence: No job can be acknowledged by the client with a 200 response unless the job is written to a Persistent storage. \nShared Resource Regional Locks: No tenant may access a regional resource without acquiring a lock on that resource in the given region. This prevents concurrent execution against the same\nresource within a region. \nCancellation Semantics: Cancelation transitions attempt to a terminal state with no guarantee of the stateful datasets the worker was manipulating.   \nExactly-once per stage: No stage will execute more than once under a single attempt_id.\nStage Order: No stage can execute out of order within a single attempt_id of a job. \n\nAPIs:\n    APIs surface splits cleanly into a control plane for specs, controls, and status and a data plane for job execution and health — all writes go through the control plane. \nControl Plane:\n    Spec:\n        POST /jobs\n        GET /jobs/{job_id}\n    Controls:\n        POST/run\n        POST /run/{run_id}:cancel  #Note: On duplicate respond respond with the idempotent key already created and status\n    Status:\n        GET /run/{run_id}:status\n        GET /run/{run_id}/stages\n        GET /run/{run_id}/stages/{stage_id}\n        GET /tenants/{tenant_id}/quota\n    Admin:\n        POST /clusters\n        GET/PUT/DELETE /clusters/{cluster_id}\n        POST /tenant\n        GET/PUT/DELETE /tenant/{tenant_id}\n        PUT/GET /tenant/{tenant_id}/clusterBinding\nData Plane: not authoritative\n   Job Execution: admit/terminate jobs from the Control Plane\n   Health: emits metrics/logs/events, health/readiness\n\n\nIdentifiers that are minted:\n Exactly-once per stage: idempotent (Job Submission Persistence + Stage Order)\n Stage Order: Provided by Job Definition\n Job Submission Persistence(job_id): Provided by the client\n        ",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "FR:\n    Jobs Definition:\n        Must support multiple ordered stages\n        Must support an immutable per build version\n    Jobs Execution:\n        Must be able to Submit and Cancel Jobs via API\n        Must be able to track execution status and stages \n        Must support configuration for retry and TTL Windows(fairness) per retry\n        Observe Job Resources(Metrics, Logs, Alerts) for Tenants\n        Must support audit\n    Tenants:\n        Must support quotas(manage runaway compute)\n        Chargeback per Hour observability for Cost Awareness emitted to global object store \n    Resource Sharing:\n        Must enforce Resource Access Control to prevent critical resources bottlenecks\n        Must enforce locking per resource region, this does not cover multi-region resource locks\n        Must support fairness queues & rate limits across tenants  \n    Clusters:\n        Configure Cluster Resources and Quotas\n        Observe Cluster Resources(Metrics, Logs, Alerts) for Platform Teams\n\nNFRs:\n    Availability: CP 99.99%, DP Globally 99.999%(w/ failover), This only includes admitted jobs only\n    RPO/RTO: CP Job Build (RPO < 1 minute, RTO < 3 hours), CP Job Scheduling ( RPO < 5 minutes, RTO < 30 minutes), CP Cluster/Tenant Config(RPO < 5 minutes, RTO < 30 minutes), DP Clusters ( RPO < 1 minute, RTO < 24 hours )\n    Scale: Multi-Region Active/Active; Tenants(100), Concurrent Jobs(p50<1,000, p99<10,000), Regional Locks; tenant scheduling budgets; resource retry budgets/circuit breakers.\n    Latency: Admitted-Jobs (p50<1 second, p95<5) from accepted response to starting job execution; On failover additional 5 minutes required. \n    Operability: Golden Signals(latency, traffic, errors, saturation) per tenant and global; budget trends create ticket; SLO Burn-Rate Paging; \n    Security: Authentication and Authorization; enforced quotas; tenant isolation; mTLS across all components; immutable audit store\n\nScope: \n    Not Included: Build system, artifact storage, approvals, UI, central observability ingestion, time-based scheduled triggers, global(not regional) shared resource locking, Jobs that span across regions\n\nInvariants:\nIdempotent Jobs: No single iteration(attempt_id) of a job can run in multiple regions. Every retry of a job is a new attempt_id of that job and is generated by the system.\nJob Retry Fairness: Retries must not preempt older admitted work by queue position across tenants \nTenant Isolation: If a tenant exceeds budget requests are rejected, never oversubscribed.\nJob Submission Persistence: No job can be acknowledged by the client with a 200 response unless the job is written to a Persistent storage. \nShared Resource Regional Locks: No tenant may access a regional resource without acquiring a lock on that resource in the given region. This prevents concurrent execution against the same resource within a region. \nCancellation Semantics: Cancelation transitions attempt to a terminal state with no guarantee of the stateful datasets the worker was manipulating.   \nExactly-once per stage: No stage will execute more than once under a single attempt_id.\nStage Order: No stage can execute out of order within a single attempt_id of a job. \n\nAPIs:\n    APIs surface splits cleanly into a control plane for specs, controls, and status and a data plane for job execution and health — all writes go through the control plane. \nControl Plane:\n    Spec:\n        POST /jobs\n        GET /jobs/{job_id}\n    Controls:\n        POST/run\n        POST /run/{run_id}:cancel  #Note: On duplicate respond respond with the idempotent key already created and status\n    Status:\n        GET /run/{run_id}:status\n        GET /run/{run_id}/stages\n        GET /run/{run_id}/stages/{stage_id}\n        GET /tenants/{tenant_id}/quota\n    Admin:\n        POST /clusters\n        GET/PUT/DELETE /clusters/{cluster_id}\n        POST /tenant\n        GET/PUT/DELETE /tenant/{tenant_id}\n        PUT/GET /tenant/{tenant_id}/clusterBinding\nData Plane: not authoritative\n   Job Execution: admit/terminate jobs from the Control Plane\n   Health: emits metrics/logs/events, health/readiness\n\n\nIdentifiers that are minted:\n Exactly-once per stage: idempotent (Job Submission Persistence + Stage Order)\n Stage Order: Provided by Job Definition\n Job Submission Persistence(job_id): Provided by the client\n        ",
      "autoResize": false,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "L8g7j5Pi1M0fFZMxFVF5B",
      "type": "text",
