      "updated": 1768832084951,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "System Design Prompt\n\nDesign a multi-region, multi-tenant job execution platform used by internal engineering teams to run\ninfrastructure workflows (e.g., data backfills, schema migrations, large batch recomputations).\n\nContext\n        •        Jobs can be long-running (minutes to hours)\n        •        Jobs may have multiple ordered stages\n        •        Teams submit jobs via API\n        •        The platform runs on Kubernetes\n        •        Regions are active/active\n        •        Some jobs operate on shared critical resources (e.g., a database, table, or cluster)\n\n⸻\n\nHigh-Level Requirements (given, not exhaustive)\n        •        Submit jobs and track execution status\n        •        Prevent duplicate execution under retries, crashes, or regional failover\n        •        Support aggressive retries with low latency\n        •        Enforce fairness and rate limits across teams\n        •        Ensure safe execution when jobs touch shared resources\n        •        Be cost-aware and prevent runaway compute\n        •        Operable at scale (observability, debuggability, recovery)",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "System Design Prompt\n\nDesign a multi-region, multi-tenant job execution platform used by internal engineering teams to run infrastructure workflows (e.g., data backfills, schema migrations, large batch recomputations).\n\nContext\n        •        Jobs can be long-running (minutes to hours)\n        •        Jobs may have multiple ordered stages\n        •        Teams submit jobs via API\n        •        The platform runs on Kubernetes\n        •        Regions are active/active\n        •        Some jobs operate on shared critical resources (e.g., a database, table, or cluster)\n\n⸻\n\nHigh-Level Requirements (given, not exhaustive)\n        •        Submit jobs and track execution status\n        •        Prevent duplicate execution under retries, crashes, or regional failover\n        •        Support aggressive retries with low latency\n        •        Enforce fairness and rate limits across teams\n        •        Ensure safe execution when jobs touch shared resources\n        •        Be cost-aware and prevent runaway compute\n        •        Operable at scale (observability, debuggability, recovery)",
      "autoResize": false,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
